ZH: 元宵节是中国的传统节日。
EN: The Lantern Festival is a traditional festival in China.
ZH: 每年的元宵节都有热闹的庆祝活动。
EN: There are lively celebrations every year during the Lantern Festival.
ZH: 元宵节通常在农历正月十五。
EN: The Lantern Festival usually falls on the fifteenth day of the lunar year.
ZH: 元宵节是春节的最后一个重要活动。
EN: The Lantern Festival is the final important event of the Spring Festival.
ZH: 人们通常会放孔明灯庆祝元宵节。
EN: People usually release Kongming lanterns to celebrate the Lantern Festival.
ZH: 在元宵节，人们会聚在一起采灯谜。
EN: During the Lantern Festival, people gather together to play lantern riddles.
ZH: 元宵节的庆祝活动集中在夜间。
EN: The celebrations of the Lantern Festival mainly happen at night.
ZH: 元宵节期间，有很多传统的食品供应。
EN: During the Lantern Festival, there are many traditional snacks available.
ZH: 元宵就是元宵节最为常见的食品之一。
EN: Yuanxiao is one of the most common foods during the Lantern Festival.
ZH: 农村地区通常会自制元宵来庆祝节日。
EN: In rural areas, people usually make their own yuanxiao to celebrate the festival.
ZH: 元宵是用糯米粉制作而成的。
EN: Yuanxiao is made from glutinous rice flour.
ZH: 很多人习惯在元宵节后拍摄一张全家人团聚的照片。
EN: Many people are accustomed to taking a family photo after the Lantern Festival.
ZH: 温暖的照明装饰为元宵节增添了节日氛围。
EN: The warm lighting decorations add to the festive atmosphere of the Lantern Festival.
ZH: 全家人常常在元宵节时一起赏灯。
EN: Families often enjoy the lanterns together during the Lantern Festival.
ZH: 元宵节是一个传统的亲友团聚的时刻。
EN: The Lantern Festival is a traditional time for family and friends to gather together.
ZH: 许多城市会举办盛大的花灯游园会来庆祝元宵节。
EN: Many cities hold grand lantern fairs to celebrate the Lantern Festival.
ZH: 孩子们喜欢在元宵节时玩猜灯谜的游戏。
EN: Children enjoy playing lantern riddle games during the Lantern Festival.
ZH: 元宵节是中国文化中重要的传统节日之一。
EN: The Lantern Festival is one of the important traditional festivals in Chinese culture.
ZH: 元宵节标志着农历新年的结束。
EN: The Lantern Festival marks the end of the lunar new year.
ZH: 元宵节是一个欢快的节日，被人们热爱和期待。
EN: The Lantern Festival is a joyous festival loved and anticipated by people.
